<br>
In any case, referring to the original post:<br>
<br>
I don't see any hindrances to you spreading information here.  You haven't been banned.  I haven't seen your posts and htreads edited by admins or deleted.  Thus, your ability to share information in these forums is unhindered.<br>
<br>
The fact that people disagree with you is not 'hindering' the ability to share information.  It just means that they don't agree.  They read your posts, divine whatever knowledge they can gain from it, weigh that against other sources of infomration or their own moralcode, and decide that they don't think thesame way as you do.<br>
<br>
If you really do have truth and fact on your side yet people disagree with you, perhaps it's not the message itself but the manner in which its delivered.  Aside from the holier-than-thou tone of your posts, I'm referring specifically to the vagueness.  You've stated previously that you are intentionally vague.  But if you're trying to prove a point, you need to give details for people to understand what you're trying to say so that you don't appear to be simply ranting.<br>
